ZH: 我昨天在街上遇上了一个老朋友。
EN: I bumped into an old friend on the street yesterday.

ZH: 他去超市遇上了他的同事。
EN: He ran into his colleague at the supermarket.

ZH: 我们在火车站遇上了一位好心的老人。
EN: We encountered a kind elderly person at the train station.

ZH: 她在学校遇上了一个帅气的男生。
EN: She met a handsome boy at school.

ZH: 我们很幸运地遇上了一场小雨。
EN: We were lucky to come across a light rain shower.

ZH: 我们在旅行中遇上了一场大雾。
EN: We encountered heavy fog during our trip.

ZH: 他们在餐馆遇上了一个非常友善的服务员。
EN: They met a very friendly waiter at the restaurant.

ZH: 我昨天遇上了一个困难的问题。
EN: I came across a difficult problem yesterday.

ZH: 他在马路上遇上了一场交通堵塞。
EN: He encountered a traffic jam on the road.

ZH: 我们在购物中心遇上了一个很大的折扣。
EN: We stumbled upon a big discount at the shopping mall.

ZH: 放心，你一定会遇上一个真正爱你的人。
EN: Don't worry, you will definitely meet someone who truly loves you.

ZH: 他在外地遇上了一个爱上的女孩。
EN: He met a girl he fell in love with while he was away.

ZH: 他在酒吧遇上了一个非常迷人的女士。
EN: He encountered a very charming lady at the bar.

ZH: 他在海边遇上了一个正在读书的朋友。
EN: He bumped into a friend who was reading by the seaside.

ZH: 我们在旅途中遇上了一场暴风雨。
EN: We encountered a storm during our journey.

ZH: 她在图书馆遇上了一个很有趣的书。
EN: She came across a very interesting book at the library.

ZH: 好巧，我们竟然在这里遇上了！
EN: What a coincidence, we actually met here!

ZH: 他不小心遇上了一个坏人。
EN: He accidentally ran into a bad person.

ZH: 他们在公园遇上了一个捡到失物的好心人。
EN: They met a kind person who found their lost items at the park.

ZH: 你喜欢看电影吗？我刚好遇上了两张免费的电影票。
EN: Do you like watching movies? I happened to come across two free movie tickets.
